<br>
First time posting here, I normally dwell on Monkly Business (being a monk and all that).  <br>
<br>
Here is my problem...<br>
<br>
We have a casual guild that on ocassion does raids.  I'm one of the raid leaders for these events.  <br>
<br>
Now, when I used to lead Halls of Testing raids, having a 60 warrior MA was often key because of the taunt cap.  But now that I'm heading into the Planes of Power I have several level tiers of warriors above 60th.<br>
<br>
So here is my question, what criterea weight the most when determining who your MA is.<br>
<br>
Here's some examples:<br>
<br>
Our highest level warrior has the poorest gear and weapons (Windblade, or 2 1handers that don't proc anything), he has AE taunt and is an Ogre.  He has the least played time of all the warriors.  He is competetant of the class, and has Main tanked many mini-bosses (POS type events) and other various baddies. (64th)<br>
<br>
Our next highest warrior has the second best weapons for taunting (wavecrasher, red epic), and I think the second best gear, he has some axp (not sure if he has AE taunt), 50 more AC than warrior number 1, and about 400-500 more hps when fully buffed.  He has tanked several bosses on raids that I've lead (Innoruuk, Doomshade, Rumblecrush, Itraeus) (63rd) (Barbarian)<br>
<br>
Our  last typical MA tank has the most experience as MA. In the past he's always performed well as the MA, and generally I rely on him to do so.  He has a will sapper and red epic, and has by far the most AXP. He also has the most experience and has tanked Tormax, Aaryonar, Sontalak, (list goes on).  I'd also wager he has the highest played time.(61st) <br>
<br>
So while this is VERY specific, feel free to give me generallities that you feel make up the most KEY factors for the level.<br>
<br>
Experience<br>
Level<br>
Gear<br>
Weapons<br>
AXP<br>
<br>
How do they rank and to what extreme?<br>
<br>
Thank you taking the time to read this, I look forward to reading the answers.<br>
<br>
+ <p><img border="0" src="http://www.personal.psu.edu/pht101/images/rolzzsig.jpg"><p><a href="http://www.cotg.net/eq">My Guild</a>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=307657">My Junk</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dinadassshnameless>DinadassSHnameless</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/16/03 10:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Help, who should the MA be...</span><hr size=1> whoever wants to? at whatever raid or whoever is around<br>
<br>
All seem to be reasonable altarnatives<br>
<br>
I'm a 60 warrior in a guild who has a 61(poorly equipped) and a 63 w/ epics. If i'm playing i normally end up MTing because the 63 is burnt out atm and the 61 is poorly equiped.<br>
<br>
go with whoever you trust, i don't see there being much of a difference between the 3. Helps to keep it rotating to keep from having one person get tired of or bored of it imo. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=140759"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.rit.edu/~rmm5333/new60.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mithrillofhalas>Mithrill of Halas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/16/03 11:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Help, who should the MA be...</span><hr size=1> they all sound like they are kinda close, and any are more than good enough to tank HOT.  use whoever is in the mood to tank and is not encumbered by RL things at the time (example would be eating, feeling sick, or as one of my quildies put it recently, having a bad case of liquid poop).  although i'd put the first one at the bottom of the list, the only thing he has going for him is extra lvl which matters relatively little since the other 2 are 60+.  but let them all get a chance to tank so they stay sharp.  <br>
<br>
if in doubt and you are facing a difficult encounter, ask your guild's top 3 clerics, they will know as well.  <br>
<br>
but to answer your question, weapons, skill, and ac/hp are your most important considerations, you need a good balance of those factors to be a good tank.  difference between a 65 and 63 is not huge if they have similar gear.  aa's are always nice, but the only big consideration you need to know about is ae taunt.  <br>
<br>
