<br>
Unless you are doing PoP encounters ,everything tanked before was done by lvl 60 tanks or below and just becaseu you have a 60+ tank doesn't mean you should use him specifically for that reason.<br>
<br>
Bad word to say on this board but if you are asking this question from the PoV of whats most effiecient for you Raid wise as a leader,Then do not over look your knights as alternatives as well should they be capable enough to do so.<br>
<br>
People often forget that when HoT was originally farmed the majority of the tanks that were tanking there were lower AC/HP wise than a nicely equipped present day Paladin let alone Wars walking into HoT now with 4k hp unbuffed for thier first time...When in the velious Era they would have been pretty damn uber walking into hot with 3k hp under over 1100 ac and no AA whatsoever...<br>
<br>
The same can be said for most velious encounters and even luclin encounters...With AA/Buffs droppable gear now it is not unheard of for a tank to walk into Ssra after only ever farming hot and never being in NToV or anything like that and having more HP than the first tanks that walked in there..<br>
<br>
Use the person that tanks best,As well the tank that the raid likes to stand behind is key to.One war may tank better than every other but if the guild doesn't have confidence in him or dislikes the way he does things it may be worse off for everyone invovled...<br>
